VALUES ('517fc056-a811-4972-a7d5-027ccb2deb9c', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'The Roman aqueducts are often praised as engineering marvels that delivered fresh water across vast distances. Their gentle, precise downhill gradient allowed gravity alone to move millions of gallons each day without a single pump. ______, some channels descended only a few inches over the course of a mile, a tolerance that taxes even modern surveyors.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Indeed,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the tiny gradient intensifies and confirms the prior claim of precise engineering."},{"id":"B","text":"Otherwise,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: it signals an alternative outcome, but the sentence reinforces the preceding point."},{"id":"C","text":"In contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the sentence agrees with and amplifies the claim of precision rather than opposing it."},{"id":"D","text":"Conversely,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Conversely'' demands an opposite idea, but this detail supports the same idea."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Identify the claim being supported
The passage praises the aqueducts'' {{yellow:gentle, precise downhill gradient}} that moved water by gravity alone.
